  "texts": [
    "• Opening hours: Online channels are mostly available 24 h a day without closing such that customers can shop at any time.",
    "This allows for spontaneous purchases but might also lengthen the purchase decision as customers can easily decide to quit and return later for purchase.",
    "In contrast, offline stores only offer limited opening hours.",
    "• Delivery: In contrast with offline channels where the customer can typically directly take the purchased option, online retail stipulates that the purchased option needs to be delivered.",
    "This might lead to issues during order fulfillment such as wrong or broken delivery or too long delivery times which in turn might lead to customer dissatisfaction."
  ],
